1.11:
That day you stood at a distance and watched.
Strangers carried off the city's wealth;
foreigners walked through the gates;
they threw dice over Jerusalem.
You stood apart and did nothing —
and that silence made you one of the invaders.

1.19:
Israel's land will overflow its ancient borders:
the southern tribes will take Edom's highlands;
the lowland people will push into Philistia;
Ephraim and Samaria's fields will be reclaimed;
Benjamin will extend east into Gilead.
